==English==
===Etymology===
From the [[w:French language|French]] ''[[frontispice]],'' from the [[w:Late Latin|Late Latin]] ''[[frontispicium]].''
===Noun===
'''frontispiece'''
# (''publication'') An [[illustration]] that is on the [[page]] before the [[title page]] of a [[book]], a section of one, or a [[magazine]].
# (''archaic, publication'') The title page of a book.
# (''[[architecture]]'') A [[façade]], especially an [[ornamental]] one.
# (''archiecture'') A small [[pediment]] of which is ornamental, especially on the top of a [[window]] or [[door]].
